		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Thuggee</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>Thuggee</b> (or <b>tuggee</b>, <b>ठग्गी</b> <i>ṭhagī</i>) (from <a href="/wiki/Hindi" title="Hindi">Hindi</a> ठग <span lang="sa-Latn" title="International Alphabet of Sanskrit Transliteration" class="Unicode" style="white-space:normal; text-decoration: none" xml:lang="sa-Latn"><i>ṭhag</i></span> ‘thief’, from <a href="/wiki/Sanskrit" title="Sanskrit">Sanskrit</a> स्थग <span lang="sa-Latn" title="International Alphabet of Sanskrit Transliteration" class="Unicode" style="white-space:normal; text-decoration: none" xml:lang="sa-Latn"><i>sthaga</i></span> ‘cunning’, ‘sly’, ‘fraudulent’, ‘dishonest’, ‘scoundrel’, from स्थगति <span lang="sa-Latn" title="International Alphabet of Sanskrit Transliteration" class="Unicode" style="white-space:normal; text-decoration: none" xml:lang="sa-Latn"><i>sthagati</i></span> ‘he conceals’)<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> is the term for a particular kind of murder and robbery of travellers in <a href="/wiki/History_of_India" title="History of India">India</a>.</p>
